property.name: text
property.value: The MapReduce system of Google employs a distributed divide-and-conquer algorithm that this demo aims to simulate. A Split actor divides the work of mapping words in the input file into a number of Map machines. (The input file is ReadTest.map in the same directory as this demo.) Those Map machines output pairs of words and value 1's to the Reduce machines, which then count the occurrences of each word. The outputs from all the Reduce machines are merged and are sent to the Display belonging to this model that generates the MapReduce system.

property.name: text
property.value: This model uses transformation attributes to demonstrate the design workflow of a configurable model. The original model (with 1 Map and 1 Reduce) serves as a minimal template that can be used to generate models of arbitrary size. The ConfigureModel attribute configures the template to generate such a model. Its parameters can be edited with "Customize" -> "Configure" from the popup menu. Its mapCount parameter controls the number of total Map actors in the configured model, and its reduceCount controls the number of Reduces. CleanUpModel is another transformation attribute to clean up a configured model to restore the template in the editor. CheckConsistency checks the structural consistency.

property.name: text
property.value: Choose "Open Transformation Controller" from the popup menu of any transformation attribute to perceive its internal design with hierarchical Ptera models. Double-click to execute it.

property.name: text
property.value: Workflow: 1) CheckConsistency, 2) run the template, 3) ConfigureModel, 4) CheckConsistency, 5) run the model, 6) CleanUpModel
